1. implict wait:
driver.manage().timeouts().implicitlyWait(Duration.ofSeconds(10));

2. explict wait
WebDriverWait wait = new WebDriverWait(driver, Duration.ofSeconds(10));
wait.until(ExpectedConditions.condition(webelement));

conditions:
1. elementToBeClickable
2. visibilityOf
3. visibilityOfElementLocated
4. presenceOfElementLocated -> DOM
5. alertIsPresent

3. fluent wait
Wait<WebDriver> wait = new FluentWait<>(driver)
  .withTimeout(Duration.ofSeconds(value))
  .pollingEvery(Duration.ofSeconds(value))
  .ignoring(Exception.class)
  .withMessage("msg");
wait.until(ExpectedConditions.condition(webElement));
